ES BY OBLIVIATOR, EPOC 6011:595.698)"}},{"data":{"text":"INITIAL SURVERY OF A MOON OF ALGERONIA 5, TRANSPERATEOUS, THE..."}},{"data":{"text":"...LANDSCAPE SEEMS TO BE TRANSPARENT ON THE ENTIRE MOON SURFACE. IT..."}},{"data":{"text":"...IS AN INTERESTING FIND. (NOTES BY OBLIVIATOR, EPOC 6011:595.715)"}},{"data":{"text":"A MOON OF ALGERONIA 7, FELISIONA, IS APPARENTLY A FELISIAN MOON. IT..."}},{"data":{"text":"...IS LABELED TO HAVE A BREATHABLE ATMOSPHERE AND IS SUITABLE FOR..."}},{"data":{"text":"...LIFE.PLANET SURVEY SHOWED MASSIVE MOUNTAIN RANGES PROBABLY..."}},{"data":{"text":"...CAUSED BY AN EXTREME AMOUNT OF TECTONIC ACTIVITY."}},{"data":{"text":"(NOTES BY OBLIVIATOR, EPOC 6011:595.717)"}}],"childrenPlanet":[{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 1","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 1","index":"01"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 1"}},{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 2","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 2","index":"02"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 2"}},{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 3","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 3","index":"03"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 3"}},{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 4","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 4","index":"04"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 4"}},{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 5","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 5","index":"05"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 5"}},{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 6","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 6","index":"06"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 6"}},{"id":"planet_ALGERONIA 7","data":{"name":"ALGERONIA 7","index":"07"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/ALGERONIA 7"}},{"id":"planet_TRANSPERATEOUS","data":{"name":"TRANSPERATEOUS","index":"08"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/TRANSPERATEOUS"}},{"id":"planet_FELISIONA","data":{"name":"FELISIONA","index":"24"},"fields":{"slug":"/planets/FELISIONA"}}]}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/stars/ALGERON"}}}